==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Adage
<hw>Ad"age</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>adage</ets>,
fr. L. <ets>adagium</ets>; <ets>ad</ets> + the root of L. <ets>aio</ets>
I say.]</ety> <def>An old saying, which has obtained credit by long use;
a proverb.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Letting ⟦ldquo⟧I dare not⟦rdquo⟧ wait upon ⟦ldquo⟧I
would,⟦rdquo⟧⟦br⟧
Like the poor cat i' the <qex>adage</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Axiom; maxim; aphorism; proverb; saying; saw;
apothegm. See <er>Axiom</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Adagial</ent>⟦br⟧
